10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to State Department of Rehabilitation
Services; appropriating certain funds in certain
12 amount for certain purpose; directing utilization of
certain amounts for certain purposes; providing for
13 noncodification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 There is hereby appropriated to the Department of Rehabilitation
20 Services from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the General
21 Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year ending June
22 30, 2027, the sum of One Hundred Eighty-six Thousand Dollars
23 ($186,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to perform the
24 duties imposed upon the State Department of Rehabilitation Services.
Req. No. 17418 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
2 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
3 Funds appropriated by Section 1 of this act shall be utilized as
4 follows:
5 1. Ninety-three Thousand Dollars ($93,000.00) shall be used at
6 the Oklahoma School for the Blind to establish and maintain a School
7 Resource Officer Program or provide physical security enhancements
8 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
9 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
10 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems; and
11 2. Ninety-three Thousand Dollars ($93,000.00) shall be used at
12 the Oklahoma School for the Deaf to establish and maintain a School
13 Resource Officer Program or provide physical security enhancements
14 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
15 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
16 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems.
17 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
18 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
